ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR Q64

The following additional terms apply to Q64: Adaptive Representational Dynamics:

1. COPYLEFT REQUIREMENT
   All modifications, derivative works, and extensions of this software must be
   released under the same AGPL-3.0 license. This includes:
   - Rust FFI bindings
   - Language bindings (Swift, C, MATLAB, etc.)
   - Performance optimizations and GPU implementations
   - Hierarchical extensions (Menger Sponge framework)

2. NETWORK USE
   If you run a modified version of Q64 over a network and provide access to
   its functionality to others, you must make the source code of your modified
   version available to all networked users under the AGPL-3.0 license.

3. ATTRIBUTION
   All distributions (modified or unmodified) must retain:
   - Original copyright notice
   - Links to original repository
   - Reference to the critical turn architecture (THE_CRITICAL_TURN.md)

4. NO ADDITIONAL RESTRICTIONS
   You may not impose any further restrictions on recipients' rights granted by
   the AGPL-3.0 license. This applies to all derivative works.

5. SCIENTIFIC INTEGRITY
   When publishing research using Q64, you must:
   - Cite the original work
   - Acknowledge the four-primitive architecture
   - Disclose any modifications to the core algorithm

